{"TopicId":185913,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Tips for a VTOL and Engine Clustering","CreatedByName":"WaitingCynicism","CreatedById":194568,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T00:35:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"WaitingCynicism","CreatedById":194568,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T00:35:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all, I am currently trying to build just a basic \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E/spaceplane/space fighter. I understand aircraft design and have seen the basic aircraft design guide, yet I just can\u0027t seem to get the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E even when I balance around \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E. Do you all have any tips for a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn another note, what engines do you all like to use for clustering for a lifter? I\u0027m trying to work on some clustered rockets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T03:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185913\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561768555\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WaitingCynicism\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, WaitingCynicism said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just can\u0027t seem to get the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E even when I balance around \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you looking at just \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E, or also center of\u00A0\u003Cu\u003Ethrust\u003C/u\u003E?\u00A0 That\u0027s the one that takes a lot more work on a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E than a normal plane.\u00A0 To get the thing to go straight up, you need the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E to go right over the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 And ideally, you want the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E to stay in the exact same place as you burn fuel, so you don\u0027t run into torque later in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WaitingCynicism","CreatedById":194568,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T21:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626929\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185913\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561778654\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165625\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aegolius13\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Aegolius13 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you looking at just \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E, or also center of\u00A0\u003Cu\u003Ethrust\u003C/u\u003E?\u00A0 That\u0027s the one that takes a lot more work on a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E than a normal plane.\u00A0 To get the thing to go straight up, you need the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E to go right over the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 And ideally, you want the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E to stay in the exact same place as you burn fuel, so you don\u0027t run into torque later in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hadn\u0027t checked \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E but I will! Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}